# --- core/otel OCB collector v0.105.0 transitive modules (pinned, no fix) ----
# The custom OCB collector is pinned to 0.105.0 for byte-identical traces (#180);
# its bundled otel/sdk (1.28.0) + grpc (1.65.0) carry CVEs fixed only in later
# releases the 0.105.0 pin can't take. The Go stdlib is patched via the go1.26.4
# toolchain bump (core/otel/Dockerfile); these clear when the collector pin moves.
# (The minimal OCB build excludes docker/docker + golang-jwt, so the old
# otelcol-contrib deferrals for those are dropped.)
CVE-2026-24051
CVE-2026-39883
CVE-2026-33186

# --- litellm wolfi base: busybox + openssl + py3-pip-wheel (Chainguard) ------
# The litellm v1.89.1 upstream image ships a Chainguard Wolfi base. A fix exists
# upstream (busybox 1.37.0-r58, openssl 3.6.3-r0, py3-pip-wheel 26.1.2-r1) but
# the patched builds are NOT in Chainguard's free apk repo yet, so an `apk
# upgrade` of these is a no-op (verified) — they clear when litellm rebuilds its
# base. busybox here is the CPIO/shell applet set and py3-pip-wheel is the system
# pip's vendored urllib3 — neither is reachable from the proxy, which runs out of
# a uv venv with urllib3 pinned to the patched 2.7.0.
CVE-2023-39810
CVE-2026-26157
CVE-2026-26158
CVE-2026-45447
CVE-2026-44432

# --- duckdb/slim bases: debian 12 base packages (no upstream fix) ------------
# core/benchmark-base-duckdb + benchmark-base-slim (#181) are debian:12-slim;
# these have no fixed Debian package (will_not_fix / affected) so apt upgrade
# can't clear them. Low real-world risk in a build-time data loader: zlib's
# MiniZip overflow (Debian won't fix), jq DoS on crafted JSON (jq only parses
# trusted HF parquet metadata here), openldap (ldap unused). Revisit on fix.
CVE-2023-45853
CVE-2023-2953
CVE-2026-32316
CVE-2026-40164
